1
00:00:41,033 --> 00:00:42,400
<i> You bastard!</i>

2
00:00:42,533 --> 00:00:43,833
<i> Miss!</i>

3
00:00:43,967 --> 00:00:44,933
<i> What are you doing?</i>

4
00:00:45,067 --> 00:00:46,267
<i>You're the one who hit someone,</i>

5
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:47,367
<i>and you've got the nerve
to be arrogant?</i>

6
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:48,800
<i> You scratched my car!</i>

7
00:00:48,933 --> 00:00:51,667
<i>Sir, how much
will the repair be?</i>

8
00:00:51,800 --> 00:00:52,767
<i> Twenty thousand pesos.</i>

9
00:00:52,900 --> 00:00:54,000
<i> Oh, my god!</i>

10
00:00:54,133 --> 00:00:55,767
<i>My godmother and I will
find a way.</i>

11
00:00:55,900 --> 00:00:56,967
<i> Hello, Paz.</i>

12
00:00:57,100 --> 00:00:58,100
<i>Why did Felma end up
at the village hall?</i>

13
00:00:58,233 --> 00:01:00,967
<i> Felma damaged someone's car.</i>

14
00:01:01,100 --> 00:01:02,567
<i>It's because she's drunk again!</i>

15
00:01:03,667 --> 00:01:05,800
<i> Thief! He took my wallet!</i>

16
00:01:05,933 --> 00:01:06,933
<i> Kid.</i>

17
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,067
<i> You went and tired me out.</i>

18
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:10,567
<i> What happened to my kid?</i>

19
00:01:10,700 --> 00:01:12,233
<i> He's at the police station.</i>

20
00:01:12,367 --> 00:01:14,300
<i>Someone filed a complaint,
theft case.</i>

21
00:01:14,433 --> 00:01:15,767
<i> Why are you accusing him?</i>

22
00:01:15,900 --> 00:01:19,767
<i>He was caught holding
Mrs. Tuazon's wallet.</i>

23
00:01:19,900 --> 00:01:21,700
<i>Could you please
forgive the child?</i>

24
00:01:22,233 --> 00:01:23,533
<i> He's begging you.</i>

25
00:01:23,667 --> 00:01:24,633
<i> And who are you?</i>

26
00:01:24,767 --> 00:01:26,000
<i> They're friend.</i>

27
00:01:26,467 --> 00:01:28,467
<i>Thank you so much, Mr. Salvador.</i>

28
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:29,267
<i> Noah.</i>

29
00:01:30,233 --> 00:01:31,767
<i> Just call me Noah.</i>

30
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:57,000
Mom, are you still mad at me?

31
00:01:58,100 --> 00:02:00,367
Sorry that I had to steal.

32
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,933
You stole something, Jeff?

33
00:02:03,067 --> 00:02:03,933
That's a crime!

34
00:02:04,067 --> 00:02:04,933
What about you, who cheated?

35
00:02:05,067 --> 00:02:07,200
Don't bring it up.

36
00:02:09,100 --> 00:02:11,200
Mom might get mad at me again.

37
00:02:12,733 --> 00:02:13,700
My dear children.

38
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:23,600
No.

39
00:02:25,467 --> 00:02:27,100
I'm not mad at you.

40
00:02:28,933 --> 00:02:33,100
You're the ones who should get
mad, because I neglected you.

41
00:02:36,633 --> 00:02:38,500
I'm trying to bounce back.

42
00:02:40,933 --> 00:02:43,967
I thought whenever I get sad

43
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:47,733
and remember what your dad
did to me,

44
00:02:49,033 --> 00:02:52,167
it was okay to get drunk
and forget.

45
00:02:54,067 --> 00:02:56,233
I thought it helped me.

46
00:02:58,667 --> 00:02:59,867
But I was wrong.

47
00:03:01,267 --> 00:03:03,200
I was being selfish.

48
00:03:03,333 --> 00:03:06,800
I forgot that I have children
who rely on me...

49
00:03:07,967 --> 00:03:10,333
and need my help.

50
00:03:15,233 --> 00:03:19,367
Yes, I need help to review.

51
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:23,033
And I miss your cooking, Mom.

52
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:25,333
The food we bring to school.

53
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:30,000
I miss doing that too, Jeffrey.

54
00:03:31,967 --> 00:03:35,767
When they threatened
to take you away from me,

55
00:03:36,967 --> 00:03:41,367
that's when I realized that
I had a lot of shortcomings.

56
00:03:44,967 --> 00:03:46,000
My dear children...

57
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:52,000
I can't bear getting
separated from you.

58
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,967
Your dad has left us.

59
00:03:56,133 --> 00:03:58,600
I can't let us get separated
from each other.

60
00:03:58,733 --> 00:03:59,733
Right?

61
00:04:00,667 --> 00:04:03,633
I can never forgive myself,

62
00:04:03,767 --> 00:04:05,733
if that were to happen.

63
00:04:05,867 --> 00:04:07,400
Always remember that.

64
00:04:11,700 --> 00:04:14,867
I'm sorry too,
for all my sins, Mom.

65
00:04:16,067 --> 00:04:19,600
I promise that
I'll never cheat again.

66
00:04:21,033 --> 00:04:23,400
I will study hard.

67
00:04:23,533 --> 00:04:26,100
Me, too, I will never steal
again.

68
00:04:32,533 --> 00:04:35,500
And I will never get drunk
again.

69
00:04:37,167 --> 00:04:38,967
Really, Mom?

70
00:04:58,567 --> 00:05:00,900
So, Noah is a good person
after all?

71
00:05:01,067 --> 00:05:05,500
I never expected he'd help us.

72
00:05:06,533 --> 00:05:08,200
Felma, earlier...

73
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:11,800
I almost sold my jewelry
earlier.

74
00:05:11,933 --> 00:05:16,800
Thank goodness Manuel sent you
some money.

75
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:18,900
He borrowed from Abel.

76
00:05:19,467 --> 00:05:20,600
He knows?

77
00:05:20,733 --> 00:05:22,533
They called me, Felma.

78
00:05:22,667 --> 00:05:25,200
Your ex wanted
to call you so badly.

79
00:05:25,633 --> 00:05:28,467
They also knew that Hazel
fought with you.

80
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,700
He'll probably explain himself.

81
00:05:32,267 --> 00:05:35,500
He'll promise again
that he'll fix things.

82
00:05:35,967 --> 00:05:37,200
And I'll get my hopes up again.

83
00:05:39,033 --> 00:05:44,333
Then his wife will call
and reproach me again.

84
00:05:45,433 --> 00:05:48,500
The problem is
that he married a witch.

85
00:05:49,133 --> 00:05:50,533
You only have two options.

86
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:53,600
It's either you put up with her
or you fight her.

87
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:57,167
If I were you, I'd fight her!

88
00:05:58,967 --> 00:06:01,700
Paz, I just want a peaceful
life.

89
00:06:01,833 --> 00:06:04,333
Especially for my children.

90
00:06:06,133 --> 00:06:11,433
That will never happen as long
as that witch is in the picture.

91
00:06:12,867 --> 00:06:14,800
There's another way for us
to live in peace.

92
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:16,700
What is it?

93
00:06:27,167 --> 00:06:29,700
I'm glad that man
didn't send you to jail.

94
00:06:31,367 --> 00:06:34,767
Mr. Salvador is a good man.

95
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:37,567
He even helped Jeffrey out.

96
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,600
I don't understand Jeffrey.

97
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:44,167
Why did he have to steal?

98
00:06:44,300 --> 00:06:46,533
He's desperate to help me.

99
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:49,333
Maybe that's how it is
when you're desperate.

100
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:51,533
You get to do bad things.

101
00:06:54,700 --> 00:06:55,833
Me, for example.

102
00:06:57,200 --> 00:07:00,100
I'm desperate to recover
from what happened.

103
00:07:01,367 --> 00:07:04,900
I thought drinking
would help me.

104
00:07:05,900 --> 00:07:07,167
But it made everything worse.

105
00:07:07,933 --> 00:07:09,267
Sorry, Felma.

106
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:12,600
You made me get used to you
always being there.

107
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:17,133
But in a snap, you were gone.

108
00:07:19,233 --> 00:07:23,233
What's worse is that, your wife
even picked up a fight.

109
00:07:24,933 --> 00:07:25,933
Sorry, Felma.

110
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:30,000
I didn't know Hazel called you.

111
00:07:30,133 --> 00:07:32,233
She forbade me from calling you.

112
00:07:32,367 --> 00:07:35,400
And from asking financial
support from you.

113
00:07:35,533 --> 00:07:37,433
Felma, Felma, no.
I will still support you.

114
00:07:37,567 --> 00:07:40,067
Okay? It's an agreement between
you and me.

115
00:07:40,633 --> 00:07:42,433
Just ignore her.

116
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:46,633
She'll keep finding a reason
to fight with me.

117
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:49,967
Manuel, she always tells me,

118
00:07:50,133 --> 00:07:51,500
that you left us.

119
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:57,667
My heart isn't as hard as stone
not to get hurt.

120
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:03,233
I'm tired of it.

121
00:08:05,033 --> 00:08:06,200
I'm done.

122
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:08,500
What do you mean?

123
00:08:08,633 --> 00:08:09,867
Let's end this.

124
00:08:11,067 --> 00:08:12,367
I'm cutting off...

125
00:08:13,167 --> 00:08:15,467
your relationship with me
and your children.

126
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:28,467
You want to cut off
my connection with the kids?

127
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:30,600
Felma, you can't do that.

128
00:08:30,733 --> 00:08:31,733
They're also my kids.

129
00:08:31,867 --> 00:08:33,433
They will just hope
that you will come home

130
00:08:33,967 --> 00:08:37,000
if you keep talking to them.

131
00:08:37,133 --> 00:08:39,067
We both know
that it will never happen.

132
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:43,033
What if your wife
gets their call?

133
00:08:43,767 --> 00:08:45,967
Hazel will probably
get mad at them.

134
00:08:47,633 --> 00:08:51,100
They're still too young to carry
this kind of burden.

135
00:08:51,233 --> 00:08:53,100
If I'm hurting,

136
00:08:53,233 --> 00:08:54,333
how much more
could this hurt them?

137
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:56,433
<i>No, Felma.
I'll talk to Hazel.</i>

138
00:08:56,567 --> 00:08:58,433
<i>I'll tell them to leave
the kids alone.</i>

139
00:08:59,767 --> 00:09:02,900
Manuel, she won't
leave us alone.

140
00:09:03,933 --> 00:09:05,433
<i> She will never leave us alone.</i>

141
00:09:06,033 --> 00:09:07,533
<i> Please have mercy on us.</i>

142
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:10,167
You've already left us.

143
00:09:10,767 --> 00:09:13,133
It's too much if we also hear
your wife's reproaches.

144
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:15,333
Felma, that can't be.

145
00:09:16,933 --> 00:09:19,633
I can't bear
not talking to the kids.

146
00:09:19,767 --> 00:09:22,067
You should've thought of that...

147
00:09:22,567 --> 00:09:24,867
before you slept
with your woman!

148
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:27,200
Wait. What...

149
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:28,867
What do you want me to do?

150
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:31,400
No, listen, I'll go home.

151
00:09:31,533 --> 00:09:33,000
I'll have a vacation,
even for a few days.

152
00:09:33,133 --> 00:09:34,567
Come on, let's fix this.

153
00:09:34,700 --> 00:09:36,033
I'll talk to my supervisor.

154
00:09:36,167 --> 00:09:38,900
If I have to sign a contract,
I'll do so.

155
00:09:39,433 --> 00:09:40,400
<i> No need, Manuel.</i>

156
00:09:40,933 --> 00:09:41,900
Enough.

157
00:09:43,533 --> 00:09:46,433
Don't make promises that you
can't fulfill.

158
00:09:47,567 --> 00:09:49,133
Let's end this.

159
00:09:49,733 --> 00:09:52,067
Wait. Hold on...

160
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,600
What will happen to the kids?

161
00:09:54,733 --> 00:09:56,833
Felma, they're still
my children.

162
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:59,567
What about Andrea?

163
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:00,700
And Jeffrey?

164
00:10:02,667 --> 00:10:04,700
And Coleen?

165
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:06,067
She's still so young.

166
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:09,600
Who will she recognize as her
father when she grows up?

167
00:10:09,733 --> 00:10:13,800
Do you think this isn't painful
for me?

168
00:10:16,033 --> 00:10:18,767
We had been together
for so many years, Manuel.

169
00:10:19,833 --> 00:10:23,567
We promised each other...

170
00:10:24,167 --> 00:10:26,567
that we'd raise the kids
together until the end.

171
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:28,400
But what happened?

172
00:10:29,667 --> 00:10:31,333
Where is that promise?

173
00:10:32,467 --> 00:10:33,500
It's gone.

174
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,300
That's why I'm asking you,
Felma.

175
00:10:35,833 --> 00:10:39,200
Let me make it up to the kids
at least.

176
00:10:39,333 --> 00:10:42,433
Yes, we need your help.

177
00:10:43,533 --> 00:10:46,100
But if your greedy wife keeps
messing with us,

178
00:10:46,233 --> 00:10:47,333
then never mind!

179
00:10:48,100 --> 00:10:49,700
What about your expenses?

180
00:10:52,633 --> 00:10:53,967
God has mercy.

181
00:10:54,633 --> 00:10:55,933
We can survive.

182
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,367
We'll get by no matter what.

183
00:10:58,500 --> 00:10:59,533
Felma...

184
00:10:59,967 --> 00:11:00,967
Felma, I want to help.

185
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:03,367
Please don't deny me that.

186
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:05,600
It'll be harder for us
to bounce back...

187
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:08,700
if we let you do what you want.

188
00:11:10,433 --> 00:11:11,767
<i> This is also painful for me.</i>

189
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:17,800
But I've made up my mind.

190
00:11:19,700 --> 00:11:21,833
Felma, don't do this to me.

191
00:11:21,967 --> 00:11:23,367
I'm begging you.

192
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,200
Felma.

193
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:28,333
I'm begging you.
Please don't do this.

194
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,833
This is the last time
I'm talking to you.

195
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,733
Don't call us again.

196
00:11:37,767 --> 00:11:39,200
Don't write us letters.

197
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:41,900
Stop giving us
financial support.

198
00:11:42,067 --> 00:11:43,700
Or anything else.

199
00:11:44,933 --> 00:11:46,067
Felma...

200
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:48,400
Felma, I love you all so much.

201
00:11:48,533 --> 00:11:50,167
I love you and the kids so much.

202
00:11:50,300 --> 00:11:52,333
Please don't do this to me.

203
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:57,100
I can't bear to lose you all,
Felma.

204
00:11:58,133 --> 00:11:59,400
I'm begging you.

205
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:04,667
That love can never be
reciprocated.

206
00:12:07,633 --> 00:12:12,067
We'll survive without you.

207
00:12:15,433 --> 00:12:17,833
Thank you so much
for all the years...

208
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:21,200
you spent with us.

209
00:12:31,767 --> 00:12:33,100
Felma!

210
00:13:10,033 --> 00:13:11,400
Jeffrey?

211
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:16,467
Son.

212
00:13:19,367 --> 00:13:21,033
What now? That's it?

213
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:23,400
I can no longer talk to my kids?

214
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:26,400
Bro...

215
00:13:27,233 --> 00:13:29,100
can you please call Paz?

216
00:13:29,233 --> 00:13:31,133
Tell her you'll talk to Felma.

217
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:34,567
Bro, even if we call Paz,

218
00:13:34,700 --> 00:13:37,767
there's nothing you can do
if Felma has made up her mind.

219
00:13:38,833 --> 00:13:40,967
I know, but they're still
my kids!

220
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:43,533
Bro, I took care of them.

221
00:13:43,667 --> 00:13:45,800
I taught them how to speak.

222
00:13:47,467 --> 00:13:52,067
Whenever Andrea has an asthma
attack, it's me who panics.

223
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:56,733
<i>Andeng! What did you do?
Felma, inhaler!</i>

224
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:00,067
<i> Andeng!</i>

225
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:05,800
And I always play basketball
with Jeffrey.

226
00:14:05,933 --> 00:14:08,167
<i>Dad, calm down! You're so good!</i>

227
00:14:09,633 --> 00:14:13,267
<i>No! It's not counted!
Not counted! No!</i>

228
00:14:17,367 --> 00:14:21,000
<i> You're so good, Dad!</i>

229
00:14:24,033 --> 00:14:25,000
And Coleen...

230
00:14:26,100 --> 00:14:28,600
I always lull her to sleep.

231
00:14:32,733 --> 00:14:34,533
Should I forget everything?

232
00:14:36,633 --> 00:14:38,233
<i> Draw more birds.</i>

233
00:14:40,300 --> 00:14:42,933
<i> There. The bird is so small.</i>

234
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:46,867
<i>How about you?
What's the answer to that?</i>

235
00:14:47,933 --> 00:14:49,500
<i> Don't ask me, I have no idea.</i>

236
00:14:49,633 --> 00:14:51,867
<i>Mom, he's thinking about
the answer</i>

237
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,567
<i> because there are no choices.</i>

238
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:55,033
<i> No choices.</i>

239
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:05,800
Felma was right, Bro.

240
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:08,633
She was right.

241
00:15:08,767 --> 00:15:10,500
I should've thought
about the consequences

242
00:15:10,633 --> 00:15:11,833
of my action before I did it.

243
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:17,167
I would've avoided Hazel
if I had only known Felma

244
00:15:17,300 --> 00:15:19,733
and I were going to break up.

245
00:15:21,833 --> 00:15:25,700
It's my fault. This is my fault!

246
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:29,333
Bro.

247
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:33,800
Let Felma cool off for now.

248
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:36,833
Give her some space.

249
00:15:36,967 --> 00:15:38,300
You'll eventually fix things.

250
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:54,000
My dear children...

251
00:15:56,767 --> 00:15:58,867
your dad and I have already
talked.

252
00:16:00,433 --> 00:16:02,567
We will no longer communicate
with him.

253
00:16:07,133 --> 00:16:09,200
Can't we call him anymore?

254
00:16:10,667 --> 00:16:13,033
You won't write him letters,
either.

255
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:15,767
Why?

256
00:16:15,900 --> 00:16:18,200
Did his wife forbid us again?

257
00:16:21,733 --> 00:16:23,067
It seems like that's the case.

258
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:26,367
Won't I be able to talk
to dad anymore?

259
00:16:27,767 --> 00:16:30,500
Will I never see his face again?

260
00:16:31,733 --> 00:16:33,067
For how long?

261
00:16:36,433 --> 00:16:37,500
I don't know.

262
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:41,667
But, Mom, I will miss dad.

263
00:16:41,833 --> 00:16:43,400
What did he say?

264
00:16:44,533 --> 00:16:45,533
They love you.

265
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:50,600
But he needs to keep
his distance

266
00:16:50,733 --> 00:16:52,533
so you won't keep hoping.

267
00:16:53,900 --> 00:16:56,467
And so that you won't get hurt
by Hazel.

268
00:16:58,267 --> 00:16:59,967
Do you understand?

269
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:01,067
No.

270
00:17:01,900 --> 00:17:03,867
I want to talk to dad.

271
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:06,633
Andrea, don't.

272
00:17:07,967 --> 00:17:09,767
His wife might get mad again.

273
00:17:10,700 --> 00:17:11,933
What about us, Jeff?

274
00:17:13,233 --> 00:17:14,400
What about us?

275
00:17:14,767 --> 00:17:16,000
Don't we have a father anymore?

276
00:17:16,133 --> 00:17:17,300
Yes!

277
00:17:18,267 --> 00:17:20,133
He already has a new family!

278
00:17:20,267 --> 00:17:21,600
They're even having a baby!

279
00:17:23,067 --> 00:17:24,500
He's not coming back anymore!

280
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,267
Dear...

281
00:17:44,300 --> 00:17:46,500
I'm here. Right?

282
00:17:49,267 --> 00:17:51,533
I'll be your father for now.

283
00:17:54,567 --> 00:17:56,633
I'll raise you.

284
00:17:57,433 --> 00:17:58,733
You and your siblings.

285
00:17:58,867 --> 00:18:00,633
Even if I'm alone.

286
00:18:04,467 --> 00:18:06,900
What if you get tired again?

287
00:18:07,367 --> 00:18:09,233
Then we will help mom!

288
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:12,333
I'll help mom become a father.

289
00:18:13,433 --> 00:18:15,167
You help her be a mother.

290
00:18:16,900 --> 00:18:18,633
Right, Mom?
We can do that, right?

291
00:18:24,667 --> 00:18:28,800
I can do it as long as you're
with me.

292
00:18:31,067 --> 00:18:31,967
I promise.

293
00:18:33,233 --> 00:18:37,967
I'll do everything to give you
a good life.

294
00:18:39,467 --> 00:18:42,300
We'll be complete again,

295
00:18:43,467 --> 00:18:46,800
even if it's just the four
of us.

296
00:18:51,967 --> 00:18:53,533
Love you, Mom.

297
00:18:53,667 --> 00:18:54,967
I love you, Mom.

298
00:20:23,333 --> 00:20:25,233
- Hello?
- Manuel!

299
00:20:25,700 --> 00:20:27,233
What are you doing?
You took too long to answer.

300
00:20:27,367 --> 00:20:28,800
Your wife is about
to give birth!

301
00:20:29,333 --> 00:20:30,033
What?

302
00:20:31,767 --> 00:20:32,800
Wait...

303
00:20:33,533 --> 00:20:34,633
Is she due to give birth?

304
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:36,733
Hazel needs you.

305
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:38,500
Go to the hospital now.

306
00:20:38,933 --> 00:20:40,633
Hurry up! Go now, okay?

307
00:21:12,167 --> 00:21:13,967
She's so beautiful, Hazel.

308
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:19,067
She takes after you.

309
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:25,900
I'm sorry for not coming home.

310
00:21:29,900 --> 00:21:30,933
I'm sorry, too.

311
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:35,067
I'm only doing what's best
for our baby.

312
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:40,200
I'll come home.

313
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:43,667
I'll help you take care
of Baby Jessica.

314
00:21:49,533 --> 00:21:50,667
Thank you.

315
00:21:52,900 --> 00:21:53,867
Manuel...

316
00:21:55,633 --> 00:21:59,400
let's start again as a family.

317
00:22:18,267 --> 00:22:19,400
<i> There you go.</i>

318
00:22:19,533 --> 00:22:21,033
<i> Okay.</i>

319
00:22:24,633 --> 00:22:26,533
Go, Dear. Go on.

320
00:22:26,933 --> 00:22:30,300
Let's do this so it keeps
moving.

321
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:36,600
Is she already asleep?

322
00:22:40,633 --> 00:22:41,400
Mom.

323
00:22:43,033 --> 00:22:44,567
Coleen has fallen asleep.

324
00:22:44,700 --> 00:22:47,000
Is there anything
I can help you with?

325
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:50,967
- No. Stay there.
- Jeff, make it delicious.

326
00:22:51,133 --> 00:22:52,467
So we can sell a lot.

327
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:54,167
Go and sing for Coleen.

328
00:22:54,300 --> 00:22:55,667
Yes, sing for her.

329
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:57,667
- I don't know how to sing.
- Rock her to sleep.

330
00:22:57,800 --> 00:22:59,500
Rock her before she starts
to cry.

331
00:23:05,900 --> 00:23:09,033
My husband is so good
at changing diapers.

332
00:23:09,167 --> 00:23:12,800
- Such an expert.
- Of course, I'm an expert.

333
00:23:12,933 --> 00:23:15,767
- Our baby behaves well.
- That's all good.

334
00:23:17,067 --> 00:23:18,233
You might wake her up.

335
00:23:19,667 --> 00:23:21,067
- Smells good.
- Hey! What...

336
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:24,000
What are you doing?
Throw it away!

337
00:23:25,067 --> 00:23:26,033
You're so silly, Manuel!

338
00:23:26,167 --> 00:23:27,533
- You do all sorts of things.
- You're so fussy.

339
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:35,567
So?

340
00:23:36,267 --> 00:23:37,767
Your dad is so good, right?

341
00:23:44,667 --> 00:23:50,167
Happy birthday to you!

342
00:23:50,300 --> 00:23:51,133
Blow, blow, blow.

343
00:23:51,267 --> 00:23:52,000
There.

344
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:56,800
Let's take a picture.

345
00:24:06,667 --> 00:24:07,667
Hold on.

346
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:09,067
I'll take a picture of you
first.

347
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:39,400
Congrats, Mom.

348
00:24:39,533 --> 00:24:41,200
Congrats!

349
00:24:41,333 --> 00:24:42,933
- Congrats, Mom.
- Congratulations!

350
00:24:45,167 --> 00:24:46,767
Wait. Let's take a selfie,
so that I can be in it, too.

351
00:24:46,900 --> 00:24:47,933
Selfie?

352
00:24:48,067 --> 00:24:49,167
Selfie, so I can be there, too.

353
00:24:49,300 --> 00:24:50,900
Is Uncle Noah going
to take a selfie?

354
00:24:51,033 --> 00:24:52,000
Yes!

355
00:24:52,133 --> 00:24:53,567
- Don't forget to airdrop.
- Such a millenial!

356
00:24:53,700 --> 00:24:54,733
Sure.

357
00:24:54,867 --> 00:24:56,667
Okay, selfie.

358
00:24:56,800 --> 00:24:58,867
1, 2, 3...

359
00:25:00,433 --> 00:25:03,233
One more, one more. 1, 2, smile.

360
00:25:04,567 --> 00:25:06,967
- There!
- He's a Gen Z! Gen Z!

361
00:25:07,100 --> 00:25:09,400
Congrats!

362
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:11,833
I know you.

363
00:25:12,333 --> 00:25:12,933
What?

364
00:25:13,333 --> 00:25:14,400
This is you, right?

365
00:25:14,533 --> 00:25:15,433
Where did you get that?

366
00:25:15,567 --> 00:25:17,433
Tell me first if this is you.

367
00:25:17,567 --> 00:25:19,233
That's me.
Where did you get this?

368
00:25:19,367 --> 00:25:20,633
Dad!

369
00:25:20,767 --> 00:25:21,800
Dad!

370
00:25:21,933 --> 00:25:24,967
Manuel, I just want to make it
clear to you.

371
00:25:25,100 --> 00:25:27,033
We'll only come home
to the Philippines

372
00:25:27,167 --> 00:25:28,767
for my mother's funeral.

373
00:25:28,900 --> 00:25:30,633
Nothing else.

374
00:25:30,767 --> 00:25:32,533
Hazel, it's been a long time.

375
00:25:32,667 --> 00:25:34,433
I'm too ashamed to face them.

376
00:25:34,567 --> 00:25:35,100
Good.

377
00:25:35,267 --> 00:25:36,300
You know what I think?

378
00:25:36,433 --> 00:25:37,900
You still haven't forgiven him
yet.

379
00:25:38,033 --> 00:25:39,367
What made you say so?

380
00:25:39,733 --> 00:25:43,067
Because it will no longer
put you in a bad mood

381
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:44,667
whenever we talk about him
if you've already forgiven him.

382
00:25:45,500 --> 00:25:46,433
I can do it.

383
00:25:46,800 --> 00:25:48,067
Turns out I actually can.

384
00:25:48,567 --> 00:25:51,233
I won't let you affect me
anymore, Manuel.
